SIMPLE: fencible
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fencible
<hw>Fen"ci*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of being
defended, or of making or affording defense.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No fort so <qex>fencible</qex>, nor walls so strong.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fencible</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fencible
<hw>Fen"ci*ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A soldier
enlisted for home service only; -- usually in the
<pluf>pl.</pluf></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fencing</ent>⟦br⟧
